(43, 12, 1, 40, 26, 6, 11, NULL, 'Connection of Events in Bethany', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' presence in Bethany, where significant events occur. The raising of Lazarus in John sets the stage for the anointing in Matthew, highlighting the importance of this location in Jesus'' ministry.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 1, 41, 11, 11, 11, 'Bethany', 'Journey to Bethany', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' movement to Bethany, highlighting its significance in the narrative. John 12:1 mentions Jesus arriving in Bethany, while Mark 11:11 describes Him going out to Bethany after entering Jerusalem.', 'parallel', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 2, 42, 22, 27, 27, NULL, 'Service and Supper Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of service in both passages. In John, Martha serves at a supper, while in Luke, Jesus emphasizes the role of the servant at the meal.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 2, 42, 10, 38, 42, 'Martha served', 'Martha''s Service and Role', 'Both passages emphasize Martha''s role in serving Jesus. In John, she serves at a supper, while in Luke, she is busy with serving when Jesus visits. This connection highlights her character and actions in relation to Jesus.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 2, 66, 3, 20, 20, NULL, 'Connection of Supper Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the act of sharing a meal, with John mentioning a supper and Revelation highlighting the invitation to sup together. This connection highlights the theme of fellowship and communion with Christ.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 2, 41, 14, 3, 3, NULL, 'Dinner in Bethany', 'Both passages emphasize a meal setting in Bethany, highlighting the social context of Jesus'' interactions. The presence of significant figures, such as Lazarus in John and Simon the leper in Mark, further connects these events.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 2, 43, 12, 9, 10, 'Lazarus was one of them that sat', 'Lazarus'' Significance in Both Passages', 'This connection highlights the importance of Lazarus as a figure who draws attention to Jesus. Both passages emphasize that people came to see Lazarus, indicating his role in the events surrounding Jesus'' ministry.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 2, 40, 26, 6, 6, NULL, 'Connection Between Bethany Events', 'Both passages describe events occurring in Bethany, highlighting significant gatherings involving Jesus. In John, Martha serves at a supper, while in Matthew, Jesus is at the house of Simon the leper, indicating a shared location and context.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
