(43, 12, 3, 42, 7, 37, 38, 'anointed the feet of Jesus', 'Anointing of Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize a woman anointing Jesus'' feet with costly ointment. They highlight the act of washing his feet with hair, showcasing deep devotion and humility.', 'parallel', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 3, 43, 11, 32, 32, NULL, 'Mary''s Humility and Devotion', 'Both passages emphasize Mary''s act of falling at Jesus'' feet, showcasing her humility and devotion. In John 11:32, she expresses her grief and faith, while in John 12:3, she demonstrates her love through anointing His feet.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 3, 22, 4, 13, 14, 'spikenard', 'Connection of Spikenard Usage', 'Both passages emphasize spikenard as a valuable substance. In John, Mary uses spikenard to anoint Jesus, while in Song of Solomon, spikenard is listed among precious spices.', 'keyword', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 4, 40, 10, 4, 4, NULL, 'Connection of Judas Iscariot', 'Both passages emphasize Judas Iscariot as a disciple who betrays Jesus. This connection highlights the role of Judas in the narrative of betrayal within the Gospels.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
